{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2023/03/sliding-puzzle-game-in-javascript/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"J. Pedro Ribeiro"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e3f43422-20fb-5698-ab95-5f983ce9e00a","excerpt":"The other day I stumbled upon a Sliding Puzzle Game on Wikipedia and I thought it would be a fun weekend project to build it in JavaScript. It runs on node soâ€¦","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6e4440d1a941d37aee6fafcac59751f7/65654/sliding-game.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 101.26582278481011%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"terminal output\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6e4440d1a941d37aee6fafcac59751f7/f058b/sliding-game.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6e4440d1a941d37aee6fafcac59751f7/c26ae/sliding-game.png 158w,\n/static/6e4440d1a941d37aee6fafcac59751f7/6bdcf/sliding-game.png 315w,\n/static/6e4440d1a941d37aee6fafcac59751f7/f058b/sliding-game.png 630w,\n/static/6e4440d1a941d37aee6fafcac59751f7/65654/sliding-game.png 872w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The other day I stumbled upon a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sliding_puzzle\">Sliding Puzzle Game</a> on <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sliding_puzzle\">Wikipedia</a> and I thought it would be a fun weekend project to build it in JavaScript.</p>\n<p>It runs on node so you can either clone the <a href=\"https://github.com/jpedroribeiro/SlidingPuzzleJS\">repo</a> and run it locally or you can use the Repl.it <em>iframe</em> to run it in your browser (just press the green button):</p>\n<iframe height=\"600\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"target vs currentTarget\" src=\"https://replit.com/@jpedroribeiro/SlidingPuzzleJS?embed=true\" frameborder=\"no\" loading=\"lazy\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe>\n<p>The keyboard controls might be a bit odd at first, and I got into a <strong>closure</strong> hell with mixing functional with global variables, but it works and that's as much effort I'm going to put on this.</p>\n<p>You can find the source code on GitHub <a href=\"https://github.com/jpedroribeiro/SlidingPuzzleJS\">https://github.com/jpedroribeiro/SlidingPuzzleJS</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Sliding Puzzle Game in JavaScript","date":"March 12, 2023"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2023/03/sliding-puzzle-game-in-javascript/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2023/01/event-target-vs-event-currenttarget/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"event.target vs event.currentTarget - What is the difference?","tags":["event","javascript"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2023/05/fetch-error-handling/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Error Handling in Fetch","tags":["fetch","javascript","error"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454","792910177"],"slicesMap":{}}